He wanted to prove that he was “something,” he said, so he didn’t disappoint everyone when they finally found out about his sexuality.
He is a two-time Olympic bronze medalist and has become a high-profile LGBT ambassador. He used his participation in this year’s Commonwealth Games in Australia to appeal for more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he stands out because he feels lucky to be able to live openly without negative consequences and wants to give others “hope”.
